<section id="fs-idm251114272" class="questions">
<exercise id="fs-idm235319456">
<problem id="fs-idm235002320">
<para id="fs-idm223407072"><link class="lo-reference" document="m68123"/>A printing company manufactures notebooks of various sizes. The company manufactures 3,000 notebooks each day. Should the company use process costing or job order costing?</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm245730144">
<para id="fs-idm228344672">The company should use process costing. Since there are many similar items, process costing is a better fit than job order costing.</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
